68
00:02:56,968 --> 00:02:58,344
[Wendy laughing]

69
00:02:58,678 --> 00:03:01,723
[Wendy] <i>Ron's family moved here in 1968.</i>

70
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:05,894
<i>My parents bought the house</i>
<i>on the street down below</i>

71
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:07,645
<i>at the same time that they were here.</i>

72
00:03:07,770 --> 00:03:09,355
<i>Ended up marrying the boy next door.</i>

73
00:03:09,439 --> 00:03:10,773
-[Ron] <i>Literally.</i>
-[Wendy] <i>Yep.</i>

74
00:03:11,024 --> 00:03:12,483
We've been married for...

75
00:03:13,151 --> 00:03:15,195
What did I--? Forty-two years.

76
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:16,279
Forty-two?

77
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:18,072
Seventy-six. Yeah, 42 years.

78
00:03:18,198 --> 00:03:20,950
So, you know, we've gotten
to the point where,

79
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:24,204
you know, even if I come home and sit here
and we don't say one word to each other,

80
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:26,164
he's just watching TV and I fall asleep...

81
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:27,832
it's a great relationship.

82
00:03:27,916 --> 00:03:29,876
We don't feel pressured to,
"Oh, how was your day?"

83
00:03:29,959 --> 00:03:30,877
"Oh, how was your day?"

84
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:33,046
You know, it's-- there's just no pressure.

85
00:03:33,129 --> 00:03:35,840
I feel like talking, I'll talk.
I don't wanna talk, I'm not gonna talk.

86
00:03:35,924 --> 00:03:38,635
<i>You know? And there's no,</i>
<i>"Well, why aren't you talking to me?"</i>

87
00:03:38,718 --> 00:03:43,056
<i>You know, so this is a great time</i>
<i>for us to tackle something new like this</i>

88
